place_description:
Summit Coffee brings award-winning craft coffee to a beautifully designed café, highlighted by tons of outdoor seating and natural light. This family-friendly store features a full coffee and espresso bar, plus draft beer, wine, locally baked pastries and more.

Summit Coffee's Birkdale store will feature live music, other events and much more.

reviews_data.review_text: Chill environment!! Great coffee and friendly staff.
Good and chill place to stop bye for coffee and if you want to do homework or any work, writing, reading, anything like that. This is definitely the place. Good food. Good drinks. Good vibes.

Horrible staff.
Internet doesn't work and nobody cares.
Will never be back at this location.
----
Internet not working can happen.
The attitude of the staff was not acceptable.
Arrogant, telling us they aren't IT specialist, insisting that everything worked...while we tried with 5 different devices.
I have requested a receipt for my gift card purchase three times and in three different ways including by phone, but

I was at this coffee shop last week and had a great experience. The staff is so helpful and friendly. I was able to bring my laptop and work for 5 hours while enjoying a yummy chai latte. Will definitely go back. Excellent customer service
This place has an amazing staff and vibe. The drinks are delicious. It is a great place to hang out and read.
Absolutely love this place. Such a welcoming staff and environment. Hands down the best iced vanilla latte.

This is a very nice coffee shop if you don't want the hustle and bustle of Starbucks. There's plenty of room sit down. The place is quiet and a good atmosphere. I saw people of laptops working or doing something. I saw small conversations going on without the loud noise level.

I really didn't want to write this review.

I've been to Summit plenty of times over the past several years - probably since their inception - in fact, we used to buy Summit coffee in bulk for events years ago, and despite the poor quality of that coffee, this review will only pertain to this coffeeshop in Huntersville.

Summit coffee has consistently provided boring, bland, and awful tasting coffee throughout every visit I've had to this coffeeshop. The espresso is overextracted and violently bitter, while the filter coffee is weak, tasting more of commodity-grade coffee with unsweetened cherry flavor added to it. I have never had a good cup of coffee from Summit.

I get it though, the vibes are nice, it's a good place to hang out or study or work, I suppose. But I can do that many other places and enjoy much better coffee while doing so.

Staff is generally friendly enough, but baristas and hosts rarely have a deep knowledge or understanding of the roasts they are serving. Summit seems more like Starbucks for people who hate corporatism than a real specialty coffeeshop.

Summit straddles the line between being that interesting-looking coffeeshop families who don't know any better go to as a treat, and being a cultural brand that also tries to make and serve its own coffee.

And I think that's where the issue lies: Summit is more concerned about upholding and presenting its brand, culture, and image than upholding standards and presenting a beautiful cup of coffee.

Go somewhere else, or if you absolutely have to go to Summit, get tea.
I had tea . It was very good.  We sat a long while without anyone hovering.

Had the $5.65 chai latte. Spicy with lots of flavors. Tasted like a sugary soup. Will I get it again? Nahhh. I'll pop next door and go to First Watch. Lots of people working there, was loud and not for me as a working location.

Not ideal for working, but great social spot. Internet does not work properly so if need to use other apps and tools other than a google search, don't bother. Was told by staff that during peak hours their internet is limited and certain pages do not work.
Dirty tables,  noisy,  coffee took over 15 minutes and then they gave it away to someone else,  made 2 other drinks then remade mine.  30 min of coffee waiting. Yikes
Delicious cappuccino with caramel syrup and almond milk. My daughter thinks the croissant is perfection.

For the first time I see a place where the service suffers from the beginning to the end. Neither greetings no goodbye are heard - that's one problem. The second trouble is when they call you to pick up coffee and you ask "is my coffee?", with passive aggression blonde girl in pink sweater answers "aha" and with rounded eyes. Teach service to your employees, at least from a basic course, start with John Tschohl's book.
"Achieving Excellence Through Customer Service." So management suffers.
Blueberry muffins and coffee can't beat it

Not bad, just pricy for a cappuccino at $8.84 with tip. I heard my 17-yr-old self from the mid-1990s, who started out making $4.25 an hour, yelling at me, "YOU SPENT WHAT FOR A CUP OF COFFEE?!?" That inflation thing again, thx Kamala Biden.
Summit coffee and service are always excellent.
Great place to visit with friends.
Great area and outdoor seating!
Waterbean is so much better don't waste your time or money coming here. Service is bad. And honestly the coffee is not good.
Coffee was good. Service was ok. Tried one of the salted caramel (taylor version) but hot. It was good and had a buttery taste. My wife's tierramisu drink was ok.
Decaf almond milk latte was........wonderful

Nice, bright space. Really needs noise dampening. The noise meter app on my phone registered a consistent 70db.

Other than that wish they have the decaf (Descent) from the Davidson location.
Best chai lattes around
Service and options as good as any coffee house or big chain stores.
Best Americano in the region. Excellent customer service!
Nice cozy place to have some good coffee or tea! Outside seating and a little play area for children!!
Great little place to chill and have some coffee.
Coffee tasted burnt.  I threw it out.

When I have to wait to be greeted & I'm treated as though I am inconveniencing someone, I won't be spending my time or money there. The girl literally looked me up & down and rolled her eyes. It does not have a coffee shop atmosphere either, it doesn't even smell like coffee, lol! What a terrible place. I walked out without ordering because I felt so disrespected.
Super nice staff, great drinks, nice vibe! Love the live music Friday nights
Super yum coffee and pastries. Friendly baristas.

The vegan chocolate chip muffin has gone way downhill. It used to be pumpkin chocolate chip and a ten out of ten. Now it's bananna and barely average. Will not return for it. (Their vegan cinnamon bun was even worse.) These recipes don't live up to the Summit Coffee standard of excellence. Sorry to be brutally honest. What a shame, because the vegan muffin used to be something to look forward to. Otherwise the place is the same and highly recommended.

We're new to the area, trying out new spots and we loved it! It's a little bit of a drive for us, but we love the Birkdale area/atmosphere and we love this coffee shop! Food was great, just wish there was a little more on the menu!
Nice little coffee spot. Perfect for a date. They even have live music
Great location, and they have open air doors.  Nice employees and comfy seats.
Summit is a super cool coffee shop. Great for small dates and studying.

Super cute place! The summit coffee near my place is super overpriced so I made sure to be careful when visiting this location. I got the blue skies seasonal drink ($5.60 for a 16 oz, pretty standard). Unfortunately the blueberry flavor was very much a "fruity pebbles" blueberry and made the drink taste less refreshing and more like I was drinking cereal milk--which is tasty, just not what I was looking for. Overall super cute and I love the vibe.
Enjoyed the atmosphere and iced matcha latte here.
My wife picked up coffee for me here on her way home and wow it was amazing ! Best coffee I've had in a while.
A delightful coffee shop with some seating. Summit has delicious coffee and the staff was so friendly!
Favorite Sunday morning hangout for coffee and friends.
Great coffee and kind staff ! Definitely recommend the vanilla latte

This was our first time here.  It is a cute place with plenty of seating outside.  Everyone was super friendly as soon as we walked in the door.  The service was super slow and it was not crowded. Our campfire coffee drink did not look anything like the picture and it was just average.  The cookie we shared and was very good. Nice place to visit.
Special drip coffee was good, hot chocolate not so much. Lots of people on their laptops restricted seating choices.
Expensive and they don't brew coffee here it gets delivered to them from some other place that makes it
My favorite place to study. The baristas are very thoughtful and it is very well managed.
Got a small strawberry matcha latte and it was very watered down and almost $8
Coffee is really good but it's super noisy (too many kids) and service can be slow.
Delicious!!!!!!!
They have the best avocado toast!! It's simple and delish. The bread they use is so yummy. I literally dream of their avocado toast!
Lovely entertainment and atmosphere

Rating score from 1 to 10
Coffee 9
Sweets or treats 2
Best coffee shop in Western NC
Fun place to pop in for a great coffee and dessert.  Sitting outside and in.
Love this place to meet with clients or colleagues. It has a lovely atmosphere, multiple seating options and tends to be less busy and loud than some other coffee shops.
Came 2 days in a row to get a mocha latte-pretty good
Drip coffee was super good and chocolate chip cookie was delicious!!
Good service.  But, if the doors to the patio are closed, this place is loud and noisy as heck.  Difficult to have a conversation.
Great cup of coffee and a pleasant environment to stay awhile.
Awesome coffee and good work vibes. Staff are very nice as well
I've only been here one time, but from that I felt as if it was just average.  Nothing special about it, but maybe it's better than that and they just weren't on their game that night.
It's very busy on the Saturday mornings that I attend, but they accommodate our meeting well.
Cool vibe and good caffeine... I mean coffee!
Love the atmosphere of this location. The indoor space feels spacious and the outdoor space is great, especially with the turf area. Coffee and tea are delicious!
Best coffee and service in Charlotte
Love the space, the coffee and the team! I'm quite literally there almost every day as it is my "office away from home." Highly recommend the coffee subscription; super good value.
Poor customer service
Had a nice latte here today. Coffee tasted great and the cranberry scone was fresh and moist. Service was fast and friendly. Will be back!
I like this coffee place. It has good food and coffee. Outdoor seating area and good space for working in your laptop.
Good capuccino, nice atmosphere for doing work inside, nice outdoor spots as well. ask for order for here to get mug instead of paper cup.

Another day I got a latte which was most  the delicious and well made latte ever. And today, we just got 2 latte and I had to open the lid to make sure that was not a normal coffee. Please wake up whoever made this today!!!!

While the location isn't bad and the shop itself is nice, it's a little hard to rate a coffee shop well when they don't even have cold brew. I settled for hot black coffee, which was good, but not ideal for starting a 10 hour drive on a hot day.
Great service and environment
Love this place - and they host yoga on Wednesday nights !

Some of the staff are just not friendly and act almost like you are bothering them by being there. Coffee is good but so expensive and I totally regretted tipping when I paid once I received such poor service after that. It's pretty and great location though w plenty of seating.

Honestly my favorite coffee shop of all time. I haven't been back in a few months. However during last school year I went there around 4 times a week. I would always order a pot of Moroccan mint tea. I love the tea so much I bought some to bring to college. However what made the Birkdale summit so nice was the people working there. They always knew my order and made my day way better.

From a coffee quality perspective, Summit has the absolute best. From an environmental perspective, Summit Coffee Birkdale Landing takes the cake. The decor is beautiful and inviting. The indoor and outdoor space are great for working, mingling, and dating. My wife and I were on the patio and really enjoyed it. There is corn hole and astroturf for adults and kids to play.

The staff here are the best in the business. The ladies working today were so kind and genuinely caring people. Julianna is fantastic and made the best cappuccino we have had yet. I always get the brew of the month and every month gets better. We are ready to go back for another cup!

Found this coffee shop via google maps. I was on a trip staying at a hotel not far from here. I will say the coffee was good. But be prepared this is a woke coffee shop. 90 degrees at 8am people wearing masks. Signs up saying they support equality transgender. I got my coffee and left.

Awful first experience!!! Baristas don't acknowledge you. When asking a simple question about my coffee I was greeted with a smart a** response. Way overpriced. I should've turned around the second I walked in. Rude, Rude, Rude!

Coffee is great! Especially the lattes. However, the customer service is easily one of worst I've seen. I go there a lot because that's how great the coffee is, but the girls do not greet you when you walk up to the registers. I know they're busy but a simple acknowledgement of  'Hi, I'll be right with you' goes a long way. Even when you're done ordering, and put your payment through, a lot of times I just stand there because they don't say anything. Again, a simple 'You're all set, Have a nice day' goes a long way.
Always a relaxing setting, good service and a great coffee
Cute spot, great baristas and smiles  . And of course the drinks are amaze!
Adorable coffee shop with plenty of space and delicious coffee.
Its good but expensive
Good coffee and friendly service! Great spot to get out of the house and work.
Best coffee shop in the area. They have wine and beer also. Live music on Fridays.
Some of the best coffee I have ever had! I really enjoyed the space (small outdoor/open air design) of the store. Will def go back when I'm in the area again!
Great service! Drink & muffin were both really good.

This is one of my favourite coffee shops in the area not only because of the coffee and ample outdoor seating, but the friendly, warm, and welcoming service from baristas Zach and Daniel. They are the reason I come back here.
The staff is amazing!!!
I love the ambiance; the service was great and fast. You can go for a coffee, wine, or beer at this place. The common area is nice. You could enjoy sitting outside or inside.
Great atmosphere, very friendly staff, and great coffee. I really enjoy coming here.
Nice coffee and ambiance. Avocado toast had too much salt in it but cortado and croissant was very good.

Update: Surprised to see the place relatively empty on a  Friday night, on a Valentine's day weekend too. The place have a live music going on, it's a great place to end a date night but the lack of patrons always baffles me. We always enjoy going here though.
-----
Have been waiting for this location to open. We love going to their Davidson location but glad that this one's finally open. This location is  modern and have a more eclectic design but the same quality offering that Summit is known for. Staff is nice. Service is good. Love the outdoor seating and the live music. A great way to end Friday. Fall drinks are also now available. For non-pumpkin latte lover, try their Orange, spice and everything nice. Free WIFI.
I ordered a latte. It was pretty on top but the milk wasn't steamed at all. Completely flat, and didn't taste very good either.
Great space, great music, and the best decaf in town. They also have good coffee and I love their oat milk hot chocolate.
Might be the worst coffee I've ever drank.
Really good coffee, friendly service.  Basecamp is my favorite.
Cold latte, limited flavors, bad coffee, americano was at least hot but still not tasty.
Cold latte, over priced, tasted terrible, weird enforcement of mask wearing in an empty business. No thanks.

Beautiful environment to just have a relaxing time. Spacious enough to allow a sizable group in. So many beautiful plants add to the homey feel of this place. The guys that took care of us were kind and friendly. Definitely coming back here.
Great coffee and atmosphere.

First timer with Summit Coffee.  Left Starbucks per government mandating their own employees to get vaccine.  THANK YOU SUMMIT COFFEE for allowing guests to make a choice (mask or not) and feeling good about purchasing coffee again.  Nice tasting coffee too.  Chai Tea Dirty Latte. Yum.
cool new coffee shop in Birkdale.  their dark roast is one of my favorites
Nice place for coffee and a treat. Warm and light interior. The salted caramel brownie is AMAZING!
Cool place, nice hip layout , inside , outside, nice tasty treats, good coffee, will be back

I've come here a few time now and love it! I've gotten the Iced Dirty Pumpkin Latte each time, and it is delicious! I know it is a seasonal Fall drink, but can't wait to find a new favorite for the winter months.
Will not serve without mask-but can be seated in large groups without mask.

Amazing space, indoor and out.  Spacious and comfortable. Baristas friendly and all wearing masks (appreciated), coffee is good and they also have a selection of wine and beer. They have avocado toast, muffins and some other small items, but as a bonus, Jason's deli and Clean juice are right there if you want something more substantial.  Great addition to the neighborhood!
I have had better coffee at a gas station
Good coffee, easy parking
Very friendly staff.
Just recently moved here and tried this place across the street from me and loved it! They have a solid coffee selection and the staff is amazing!
Chris was amazing, welcoming and fast. Great service and great atmosphere.
Awesome vibe, outdoor, live music.  My new favorite place...

The mocha latte I got was very tasty and I'd absolutely come back. But....the 2 gentlemen who were working the counter had great customer service, and that is HUGE! Can't wait to come back. Thank you for the experience.

I just had to say thank you for the great experience my wife and myself had this past Friday. I was driving by when I heard someone singing my wife and I decided that we should get our coffee and snacks there. We were so impressed with the singer's great voice and the so many variety of songs she had, we stayed longer then we anticipated wow!! We loved her what an incredible voice I think her name was Marie or Maria, either way she's fantastic we hope to go back soon. Now we are always looking when we drive by just to if she's singing congrats on your great service keep up the good work we be back Friday hope you have her back soon thanks.

Combination coffee, wine and hard cider shop/hang out.

Vibe is coastal with pale green / blue hues and lots of sunlight. Communal Picnic table set up inside.

Coffee has nice flavor, server polite. Prices were good.

Cups would not accept lid so open cup coffee to go while driving...not a good idea.
Had a very delicious small whole milk latte so glad this location has finally opened just as good as the original in davidson.  Nice relaxing atmosphere, the live music was a welcome touch
Best Coffee I've had in this area!
This spot is amazing. Atmosphere is phenomenal and the coffee is superb. Exactly as it should be.

Exceptional atmosphere, coffee, and people! Definitely get their Summit Coffee app, which currently includes a $5 credit towards your first order. I've always been a fan of their sister stores in Asheville and Davidson, and this one lives up to the hype!
